#: src/qalc.cc:7025
msgid ""
"Implicit multiplication does not differ from explicit multiplication "
"(\"12/2(1+2) = 12/2*3 = 18\", \"5x/5y = 5*x/5*y = xy\")."
msgstr ""
"Die implizite Multiplikation unterscheidet sich nicht von der expliziten "
"Multiplikation(\"12/2(1+2) = 12/2*3 = 18\", \"5x/5y = 5*x/5*y = xy\")."

#: src/qalc.cc:7028
msgid ""
"Implicit multiplication is parsed before explicit multiplication "
"(\"12/2(1+2) = 12/(2*3) = 2\", \"5x/5y = (5*x)/(5*y) = x/y\")."
msgstr ""
"Implizite Multiplikation wird vor der expliziten Multiplikation analysiert "
"(\"12/2(1+2) = 12/(2*3) = 2\", \"5x/5y = (5*x)/(5*y) = x/y\")."

#: src/qalc.cc:7031
msgid ""
"The default adaptive mode works as the \"implicit first\" mode, unless "
"spaces are found (\"1/5x = 1/(5*x)\", but \"1/5 x = (1/5)*x\"). In the "
"adaptive mode unit expressions are parsed separately (\"5 m/5 m/s = (5*m)/"
"(5*(m/s)) = 1 s\")."
msgstr ""
"Der standardmäßige adaptive Modus arbeitet wie der Modus \"implicit first\", "
"sofern keine Leerzeichen gefunden werden (\"1/5x = 1/(5*x)\", but \"1/5 x = "
"(1/5)*x\"). Im adaptiven Modus werden Einheitenausdrücke separat analysiert "
"(\"5 m/5 m/s = (5*m)/(5*(m/s)) = 1 s\")."

#: src/qalc.cc:7033
msgid ""
"Function arguments without parentheses are an exception, where implicit "
"multiplication in front of variables and units is parsed first regardless of "
"mode (\"sqrt 2x = sqrt(2x)\")."
msgstr ""
"Eine Ausnahme bilden Funktionsargumente ohne Klammern, bei denen die "
"implizite Multiplikation vor Variablen und Einheiten zuerst analysiert wird, "
"unabhängig von mode (\"sqrt 2x = sqrt(2x)\")."

#: src/qalc.cc:7036
msgid ""
"Parse expressions using reverse Polish notation (\"1 2 3+* = 1*(2+3) = 5\")"
msgstr ""
"Analysieren von Ausdrücken in umgekehrter polnischer Notation (\"1 2 3+* = "
"1*(2+3) = 5\")"

#: src/qalc.cc:7039
msgid ""
"Perform operations from left to right, like the immediate execution mode of "
"a traditional calculator (\"1+2*3 = (1+2)*3 = 9\")"
msgstr ""
"Operationen von links nach rechts ausführen, wie der sofortige "
"Ausführungsmodus eines traditionellen Taschenrechners (\"1+2*3 = (1+2)*3 = "
"9\")"

